-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Personality</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Personality Traits</h2></div></div><div class=\"flex flex-wrap gap-2\"><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Kind</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Just</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Peaceful</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">Brave</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">V = Virtuous</span><span class=\"rounded-full bg-emerald-50 px-3 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-emerald-800 ring-1 ring-emerald-100\">D = Dutiful</span></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-book-text h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M4 19.5v-15A2.5 2.5 0 0 1 6.5 2H19a1 1 0 0 1 1 1v18a1 1 0 0 1-1 1H6.5a1 1 0 0 1 0-5H20\"></path><path d=\"M8 11h8\"></path><path d=\"M8 7h6\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Spiritual</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Spiritual Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-amber-50 p-4 text-slate-800 leading-7\">In Quranic context, Khalid refers to the eternal nature of God&#x27;s promise and the eternal life</div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-shield h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M20 13c0 5-3.5 7.5-7.66 8.95a1 1 0 0 1-.67-.01C7.5 20.5 4 18 4 13V6a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c2 0 4.5-1.2 6.24-2.72a1.17 1.17 0 0 1 1.52 0C14.51 3.81 17 5 19 5a1 1 0 0 1 1 1z\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Cultural Context</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Cultural Significance</h2></div></div><div class=\"space-y-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">The name Khalid has a deep and rich cultural history within the Islamic world. In the early Islamic era, there were several prominent figures with the name Khalid, most notably Khalid ibn al-Walid, who was one of the greatest military commanders in Islamic history. His conquests helped establish the early Islamic empire and secure its territories. The name Khalid has also been the given name of many renowned scholars, poets, and leaders throughout Islamic history. It carries a sense of strength, honor, and leadership.</div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\">In Islamic tradition, Khalid carries a deep spiritual meaning. The name comes from the Arabic word &quot;khhalida,&quot; which means &quot;eternal&quot; or &quot;everlasting.&quot; This spiritual significance is reflected in the character and deeds of Khalid ibn al-Walid, who, despite his military exploits, is also remembered for his deep faith and devotion to Allah. The name Khalid thus signifies the eternal and never-ending nature of Allah&#x27;s mercy and love towards His creation. It is a reminder of the eternal and everlasting blessings that come from Allah, and the importance of living a life that seeks to please Him and attain eternal salvation.</div><p class=\"rounded-3xl bg-emerald-50 p-4 text-sm text-emerald-800\">Traditional Islamic naming context<!-- --> — Traditional Islamic name with deep spiritual significance in Islamic culture</p></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-center justify-center rounded-2xl bg-amber-100 text-amber-700 shadow-sm\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"24\" height=\"24\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\" fill=\"none\" stroke=\"currentColor\" stroke-width=\"2\" stroke-linecap=\"round\" stroke-linejoin=\"round\" class=\"lucide lucide-trending-up h-5 w-5\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><path d=\"M16 7h6v6\"></path><path d=\"m22 7-8.5 8.5-5-5L2 17\"></path></svg></div><div><p class=\"text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-slate-500\">Popularity</p><h2 class=\"text-xl font-semibold\">Popularity by Region</h2></div></div><div class=\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4 text-slate-700 leading-7\"><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Saudi Arabia</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->87</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Pakistan</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->73</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">UAE</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->83</span></div><div class=\"flex justify-between py-2 border-b border-slate-200 last:border-0\"><span class=\"font-medium\">Egypt</span><span class=\"text-slate-600\">Score: <!-- -->70</span></div></div></section><section class=\"nv-card\"><div class=\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\"><div class=\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-ce