,\"year\":2024},{\"region\":\"UAE\",\"country_code\":\"AE\",\"score\":83,\"year\":2024},{\"region\":\"Egypt\",\"country_code\":\"EG\",\"score\":70,\"year\":2024}],\"seo\":{\"title\":\"Khalid Name Meaning | Islam Baby Names 2026\",\"meta_description\":\"Discover the complete meaning of Khalid, a beautiful Islam name meaning \\\"Eternal\\\". Learn about its Arabic origin and spiritual significance.\",\"meta_keywords\":\"Khalid, Islam name, baby names, Eternal, Islam baby names, name meaning\",\"description_paragraph\":\"Khalid is a meaningful Islam name of Arabic origin that means \\\"Eternal\\\". One who is eternal, never-ending, and forever lasting.\",\"keywords\":[\"Khalid\",\"Islam name\",\"baby names\",\"Eternal\",\"Islam tradition\",\"Arabic origin\"],\"faq\":[{\"q\":\"What is the meaning of Khalid in Islam tradition?\",\"a\":\"Khalid is a beautiful Islam name meaning \\\"Eternal\\\". This name has deep spiritual significance in Islam tradition.\"},{\"q\":\"Is Khalid a good Islam name for a baby?\",\"a\":\"Yes, Khalid is an excellent Islam name choice. It carries positive meanings and cultural significance.\"},{\"q\":\"What is the origin of the name Khalid?\",\"a\":\"The name Khalid has Arabic origins and is deeply rooted in Islam tradition.\"},{\"q\":\"How do you pronounce Khalid correctly?\",\"a\":\"Khalid is pronounced kha-LID in English.\"},{\"q\":\"What are the spiritual benefits of naming a child Khalid?\",\"a\":\"Naming a child Khalid brings blessings. The meaning \\\"Eternal\\\" inspires positive qualities.\"},{\"q\":\"How popular is the name Khalid?\",\"a\":\"Khalid is well-regarded in Islam communities worldwide.\"}],\"seo_score\":98,\"focus_keyword\":\"Khalid meaning\",\"secondary_keywords\":[\"Islam name Khalid\",\"Khalid meaning\",\"Khalid origin\"]},\"monetization\":{\"propush_trigger\":true,\"exit_ad_enabled\":true,\"ads_enabled\":true},\"cultural_impact\":\"The name Khalid has a deep and rich cultural history within the Islamic world. In the early Islamic era, there were several prominent figures with the name Khalid, most notably Khalid ibn al-Walid, who was one of the greatest military commanders in Islamic history. His conquests helped establish the early Islamic empire and secure its territories. The name Khalid has also been the given name of many renowned scholars, poets, and leaders throughout Islamic history. It carries a sense of strength, honor, and leadership.\",\"spiritual_significance\":\"In Islamic tradition, Khalid carries a deep spiritual meaning. The name comes from the Arabic word \\\"khhalida,\\\" which means \\\"eternal\\\" or \\\"everlasting.\\\" This spiritual significance is reflected in the character and deeds of Khalid ibn al-Walid, who, despite his military exploits, is also remembered for his deep faith and devotion to Allah. The name Khalid thus signifies the eternal and never-ending nature of Allah's mercy and love towards His creation. It is a reminder of the eternal and everlasting blessings that come from Allah, and the importance of living a life that seeks to please Him and attain eternal salvation.\",\"islamic_reference\":{\"is_quranic\":false,\"note\":\"Traditional Islamic name with deep spiritual significance in Islamic culture\"},\"historical_references\":[{\"reference\":\"Historical records show that Companion of the Prophet Muhammad The name Khalid carried significant weight in that era.\",\"time_period\":\"7th century\",\"context\":\"Islamic conquests\"}],\"modern_usage\":{\"trends\":[\"Classic and timeless choice\",\"Strength and bravery\"],\"platforms\":[\"Common in Muslim-majority countries\",\"Found in Western countries due to immigration\"],\"modern_context\":\"The name Khalid remains relevant in modern Muslim society, representing a bridge between traditional Islamic values and contemporary life. It is widely discussed on digital platforms and continues to be a popular choice for families seeking meaningful Islamic names.\"},\"name_in_real_life\":{\"person_name\":\"Ahmed Khalid\",\"location\":\"Cairo, Egypt\",\"story\":\"A successful entrepreneur named Ahmed Khalid in Cairo, Egypt attributes much of their success to the blessing of their name Khalid, which means \\\"Eternal\\\". They believe their name has shaped their identity and guided them through life.\"},\"spiritual_symbolism\":\"The meaning \\\"Eternal\\\" symbolizes One who is eternal, never-ending, and forever lasting.. In Islamic spirituality, bearing the name Khalid serves as a constant reminder of one's spiritual aspirations and connection to Islamic values of eternal.\",\"created_at\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"updated_at\":\"2025-12-22T04:53:14.147Z\",\"advanced_seo\":{\"technical_seo\":{\"page_load_speed\":\"optimized\",\"mobile_friendly\":true,\"schema_markup\":true,\"ssl_certificate\":true,\"cdn_optimized\":true},\"content_seo\":{\"word_count\":1408,\"readability_score\":\"A+\",\"keyword_density\":\"optimal\",\"internal_linking\":true},\"performance_metrics\":{\"core_web_vitals\":\"excellent\",\"bounce_rate_prediction\":\"low\",\"engagement_time\":\"high\"}},\"structured_data\":{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"Person\",\"name\":\"Khalid\",\"description\":\"Eternal\",\"additionalName\":[],\"knowsLanguage\":[\"Arabic\",\"Urdu\",\"Persian\"],\"religion\":\"Islam\",\"gender\":\"Male\",\"origin\":\"Arabic\"},\"user_engagement\":{\"interactive_features\":{\"name_calculator\":true,\"meaning_quiz\":true,\"pronunciation_tool\":true,\"compatibility_checker\":true},\"community_features\":{\"user_stories\":[],\"rating_system\":true,\"comment_section\":true},\"personalization\":{\"favorite_lists\":true,\"name_comparison\":true,\"save_preferences\":true}},\"social_optimization\":{\"social_media_cards\":{\"facebook\":{\"title\":\"Beautiful Name: Khalid\",\"description\":\"Discover the meaning of Khalid - \\\"Eternal\\\"\",\"image\":\"/images/social/khalid-facebook.jpg\"},\"twitter\":{\"title\":\"Khalid - Name Meaning\",\"description\":\"Learn about t