ion: kha-LID. Lucky number: 6.\\\",\\\"alternateName\\\":[\\\"خالد\\\",\\\"खालिद\\\"],\\\"additionalProperty\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Origin\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Arabic\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Religion\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Islamic\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Language\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Arabic, Urdu, Persian, Hindi, English, Pashto\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Gender\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Male\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Pronunciation\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"kha-LID\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Lucky Number\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"6\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Lucky Day\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Friday\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Lucky Colors\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Red, Blue\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"PropertyValue\\\",\\\"name\\\":\\\"Personality Traits\\\",\\\"value\\\":\\\"Kind, Just, Peaceful, Brave, V = Virtuous, D = Dutiful\\\"}]}\"}}]\ne:T848,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"ScholarlyArticle\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/islamic/khalid#scholarly-article\",\"headline\":\"Khalid — Name Meaning, Origin & Cultural Context | NameVerse\",\"name\":\"Khalid — Name Meaning and Origin\",\"description\":\"Name meaning and origin analysis for Khalid: Arabic origin, Islamic context, pronunciation, lucky number, translations, personality traits, and cultural references.\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/islamic/khalid\",\"image\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"dateModified\":\"2025-12-22T04:53:14.147Z\",\"inLanguage\":\"en\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/#organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"},\"publisher\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/#organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\",\"description\":\"NameVerse is a cultural name knowledge base for name meanings, origins, pronunciation, lucky numbers, and naming context.\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\",\"logo\":{\"@type\":\"ImageObject\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/logo.png\",\"width\":512,\"height\":512},\"sameAs\":[\"https://twitter.com/NameVerseOfficial\",\"https://facebook.com/NameVerse\",\"https://instagram.com/nameverse\",\"https://linkedin.com/company/nameverse\"],\"foundingDate\":\"2025\",\"numberOfEmployees\":{\"@type\":\"QuantitativeValue\",\"minValue\":5,\"maxValue\":20},\"contactPoint\":{\"@type\":\"ContactPoint\",\"contactType\":\"customer support\",\"email\":\"hello@nameverse.com\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/contact\"}},\"mainEntityOfPage\":{\"@type\":\"WebPage\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/islamic/khalid#webpage\"},\"about\":{\"@type\":\"DefinedTerm\",\"@id\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/islamic/khalid#name-term\",\"name\":\"Khalid\",\"description\":\"Eternal\"},\"articleSection\":\"Name Meaning\",\"keywords\":\"Khalid meaning, Khalid origin, Arabic linguistics, Islamic names, pronunciation, lucky number, cultural context\",\"wordCount\":500,\"citation\":{\"@type\":\"CreativeWork\",\"name\":\"NameVerse — Cultural Name Knowledge Base\",\"url\":\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\"}}6:[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"id\":\"scholarly-article-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$e\"}}]\nf:T1fe6,{\"@context\":\"https://schema.org\",\"@type\":\"FAQPage\",\"mainEntity\":[{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What does Khalid mean?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The islamic boy name Khalid translates to \\\"Eternal\\\" from its Arabic roots. This meaning reflects the cultural values embedded in islamic naming traditions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the origin of the name Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Khalid traces its etymological roots to Arabic, with documented usage in Arabic and Urdu and Persian and Hindi and English and Pashto. This islamic name reflects centuries of cross-cultural naming exchange.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Is Khalid a boy, girl, or unisex name?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Khalid is listed as Male in islamic naming records. Parents should note that gender classification of names can differ by region and cultural context.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How do you pronounce Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Speakers pronounce Khalid as \\\"kha-LID\\\" (/ˈxɑːlɪd/). This articulation maintains the Arabic sound structure while adapting to English phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the phonetic transcription of Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Phonetically, Khalid is transcribed as /ˈxɑːlɪd/. The IPA representation helps linguists and language learners capture the name's authentic Arabic pronunciation.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the lucky associations for Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"For Khalid, Arabic naming lore specifies lucky number 6, Friday as the auspicious day, Red, Blue as favourable colors, and Ruby as the protective stone. Such details are traditional rather than scientific.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the numerology of Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In numerology, Khalid corresponds to the number 6, with Friday as a significant day, and Ruby as a related gemstone. Numerological analysis assigns meaning based on letter values and phonetic structure.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What personality traits are associated with Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names like Khalid in islamic tradition carry connotations of Kind, Just, Peaceful, Brave. These personality associations connect the name's meaning to expected character qualities.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the cultural significance of Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Within islamic tradition, Khalid carries cultural weight beyond its literal meaning. Its Arabic origins and definition \\\"Eternal\\\" position it as a name that connects heritage to contemporary identity. The name Khalid has a deep and rich cultural history within the Islamic world. In the early Islamic era, there were several prominent figures with the name Khalid, most notably Khalid ibn al-Walid, who was one of the greatest military commanders in Islamic history. His conquests helped establish the early Islamic empire and secure its territories. The name Khalid has also been the given name of many renowned scholars, poets, and leaders throughout Islamic history. It carries a sense of strength, honor, and leadership.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What is the spiritual meaning of Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In spiritual terms, Khalid carries the meaning \\\"Eternal\\\". islamic sources elaborate that in Quranic context, Khalid refers to the eternal nature of God's promise and the eternal life\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What names are similar to Khalid?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Names related to Khalid include kabir, kashish, kayan. These share Arabic linguistic roots and often carry comparable meanings or phonetic patterns.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What category does Khalid belong to?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The name Khalid falls under the \\\"Islamic\\\" category within islamic naming classifications. This categorisation helps parents find names that match their thematic preferences.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Khalid written in Arabic?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Khalid appears in Arabic as \\\"خالد تعني الباقي أو الدائم في اللغة العربية\\\". This adaptation preserves the name's essential character while conforming to arabic orthographic rules.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Khalid written in English?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"The English equivalent of Khalid is \\\"Eternal, immortal, or perpetual\\\". Such translations show how the name transcends linguistic boundaries while retaining its fundamental meaning.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"How is Khalid written in Urdu?\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"},\"answerCount\":1,\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"In Urdu, the name Khalid is written as \\\"خالد کا مطلب ہوتا ہے مستقل یا باقی رہنے والا\\\". This rendering adapts the name's sound and meaning to urdu script and phonetic conventions.\",\"datePublished\":\"2025-12-22T19:19:49.788Z\",\"author\":{\"@type\":\"Organization\",\"name\":\"NameVerse\"}}}]}7:[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"id\":\"faq-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"$f\"}}]\n8:[\"$\",\"$L2\",null,{\"id\":\"breadcrumb-schema\",\"type\":\"application/ld+json\",\"dangerouslySetInnerHTML\":{\"__html\":\"{\\\"@context\\\":\\\"https://schema.org\\\",\\\"@type\\\":\\\"BreadcrumbList\\\",\\\"itemListElement\\\":[{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":1,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Home\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":2,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Islamic Names\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/religion/islamic/1\\\"},{\\\"@type\\\":\\\"ListItem\\\",\\\"position\\\":3,\\\"name\\\":\\\"Khalid\\\",\\\"item\\\":\\\"https://nameverse.vercel.app/names/islamic/khalid\\\"}]}\"}}]\n9:[\"$\",\"main\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-page min-h-screen\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-container nv-section\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"nav\",null,{\"aria-label\":\"Breadcrumb\",\"className\":\"mb-6\",\"children\":[\"$\",\"ol\",null,{\"className\":\"flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-sm text-slate-500\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"li\",\"/-0\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"href\":\"/\",\"className\":\"font-medium text-slate-600 transition-colors hover:text-slate-900\",\"children\":\"Home\"}],[\"$\",\"span\",null,{\"className\":\"text-slate-300\",\"children\":\"/\"}]]}],[\"$\",\"li\",\"/names-1\",{\"className\":\"flex items-center gap-2\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"$L10\",null,{\"href\":\"/names