ate-700 leading-7\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"The name Khalid has a deep and rich cultural history within the Islamic world. In the early Islamic era, there were several prominent figures with the name Khalid, most notably Khalid ibn al-Walid, who was one of the greatest military commanders in Islamic history. His conquests helped establish the early Islamic empire and secure its territories. The name Khalid has also been the given name of many renowned scholars, poets, and leaders throughout Islamic history. It carries a sense of strength, honor, and leadership.\"}],[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-slate-50 p-4\",\"children\":\"In Islamic tradition, Khalid carries a deep spiritual meaning. The name comes from the Arabic word \\\"khhalida,\\\" which means \\\"eternal\\\" or \\\"everlasting.\\\" This spiritual significance is reflected in the character and deeds of Khalid ibn al-Walid, who, despite his military exploits, is also remembered for his deep faith and devotion to Allah. The name Khalid thus signifies the eternal and never-ending nature of Allah's mercy and love towards His creation. It is a reminder of the eternal and everlasting blessings that come from Allah, and the importance of living a life that seeks to please Him and attain eternal salvation.\"}],[\"$\",\"p\",null,{\"className\":\"rounded-3xl bg-emerald-50 p-4 text-sm text-emerald-800\",\"children\":[\"Traditional Islamic naming context\",\" — Traditional Islamic name with deep spiritual significance in Islamic culture\"]}],\"$undefined\",\"$undefined\",\"$undefined\"]}]]}]\n2d:[\"$\",\"$L3a\",null,{\"className\":\"my-6\",\"minHeight\":\"90px\",\"instanceId\":\"name-detail-mid\"}]\n2e:[\"$\",\"section\",null,{\"className\":\"nv-card\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"mb-5 flex items-start gap-3 text-slate-900\",\"children\":[[\"$\",\"div\",null,{\"className\":\"flex h-11 w-11 shrink-0 items-ce